e as per their mood.\n\n\n## How we built it\n\n- HTML\n- CSS\n- Javascript\n- Face API\n- Figma\n- Deep Learning\n\n\n## Loading Screen\n\n![Image description](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/0c1fypxp1uzqvh21cnmj.png)\n\n&nbsp;\n\n## Landing Screen\n\n![Image description](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/4mt17i9vqscatymfe13o.png)\n\n\n## Mood Selection Page\n\n![Image description](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/dkwuh8bk7ksxced0e9vo.png)\n\n\n## About us Page\n\n![Image description](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/q9t5tyjhkww3bg99s4yz.png)\n\n\n## Challenges we faced\n\nA major challenge that we encountered was finding a correct API to be integrated to retrieve the expressions of the user, basically using AI. Even, after we found an API called 'Face-API', it was tough for us to predict the exact expressions of the user, and redirect them to the respective page. Also, finding the best-suited assets and resources to be used in the web app, was absolutely a challenge.\n\n\n## Accomplishments that we're proud of\n\n- We built the web app from scratch beginning with designing the entire UI on Figma and then we progressively coded it.\n- We made the website fully responsive to provide the best user experience from scratch.\n- One of the accomplishments that we are absolutely proud of is that the way we managed to retrieve the final predicted expression, because that API doesn't provide us a direct way to do so.\n\n\n## What we learned\n\n- Integration of Face APIs in JS\n- Figma Prototyping\n- Code Optimization\n- Elevation of UI & UX\n\n\n## What's next for Peace In Space\n\n- More resources with random selection in emotion recommendations\n- Improvement in APIs & ML Model\n- Switching to TF.js & OpenCV\n- Taking the whole codebase to React ( for dynamic CMS )\n\n\n## Hackathon Winner\n\n> **Best Space App powered by US Space Force** at Peace Out Hacks organized by MLH (**